==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: moor fowl
<hw>moor fowl</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A reddish-brown grouse (<spn>Lagopus
Scoticus</spn>) of upland moors of Great Britain; the European
ptarmigan, or <altname>red grouse</altname>, also called the
<altname>moorgame</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> red grouse, moorbird, moorgame, <spn>Lagopus
scoticus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The European heath grouse. See under
<er>Heath</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>moorgame</ent>⟦br⟧
